Difference between BPE and SentencePiece?

Core Architecture DifferencesHandling of Whitespace: BPE requires pre-tokenized text. 
It splits sentences into words using spaces first, then builds subwords. SentencePiece treats the entire input string as a raw byte/character stream. 
It replaces spaces with a special meta-symbol (like _) and tokenizes directly.Vocabulary Initialization: BPE begins its vocabulary construction with a base character set extracted purely from the dataset text. 
SentencePiece initializes its base vocabulary using a pre-determined model structure, typically using Unigram language modeling or BPE over raw bytes.Out-of-Vocabulary (OOV) Protection: BPE can fail or throw OOV errors if it encounters completely unseen characters in new test data. 
SentencePiece completely eliminates OOV errors by falling back to byte-level tokenization for unknown symbols.
